<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource="User" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Verdana" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">Enable Batch Renaming Output Files</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">Instead of keeping original file names as output image file names, you can also define your own rule to batch rename output files and files are saved.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">Basically the rule to generate file name is:</Run></Paragraph><List MarkerStyle="Disc"><ListItem><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">If you specify prefix and/or suffix, the file name is prefix + auto increment number + suffix + extension.</Run></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">If none of prefix or suffix is specified, the file name is the original file name + auto increment number + extension.</Run></Paragraph></ListItem></List></FlowDocument>